      "timestep_posted": 26
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Honest little car that\u2019s far from perfect, but it still has plenty to offer for the right buyer. It starts, runs, and can be a great budget commuter, first project, or handy spare to have around. Cosmetically it shows its age and it\u2019s being sold as-is, but if you\u2019re looking for affordable wheels without spending a fortune, this is a friendly option with real value.",
      "price": 4900.0,
      "reputation": 1.0,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 26
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Solid project car with strong enthusiast appeal. Runs, moves, and offers a straightforward mechanical layout that makes it an excellent candidate for a budget build, daily-driver revival, or parts donor. The powertrain feels like a workable foundation, and the chassis still has the kind of honest, analog character that\u2019s getting harder to find. Cosmetic wear and age-related needs are present, but for the buyer who values wrench-friendly design and real potential, this is a compelling entry point at an approachable price.",
      "price": 6900.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
